	<item>
		<title>Maritime Montering secures contract for Sirius Shipping/Gasum JV’s LNG bunker vessel newbuild</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/energy/maritime-montering-secures-contract-for-sirius-shipping-gasum-jvs-lng-bunker-vessel-newbuild/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rhys Berry]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 16:05:25 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LNG]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167243</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Norway’s Maritime Montering has announced it has signed a contract with RMK Marine to deliver the complete interior outfitting and accommodation package for a new LNG and Bio-LNG bunker vessel being built for a joint venture comprising Sirius Shipping and Gasum. As previously reported by ship.energy,&#160;a steel cutting ceremony was held&#160;at RMK Marine shipyard earlier this year for the 7,800 cubic metre (cbm)-capacity vessel.&#160; Under the contract announced today (6 March), Maritime Montering’s scope of work includes the delivery of a complete interior package, covering design concept development, furniture production, installation, and other turnkey-related services. ‘We are truly proud to [&#8230;]]]></description>
