		<item>
		<title>Sempra pulls plug on Topolobampo LNG project</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/energy/sempra-pulls-plug-on-topolobampo-lng-project/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ian Taylor]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 12:39:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LNG]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167213</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[US-heaquarted energy player Sempra has cancelled its planned involvement in the Vista Pacifico LNG liquefaction export facility. Sempra Infrastructure Partners (SIP) was looking to develop the plant near the Port of Topolobampo in Sinaloa, Mexico with the country’s state-owned electric utility Comisión Federal de Electricidad (CFE). In a short update included in its 2025 annual report published on 26 February, Sempra said: ‘Due to a change in SI Partners’ and the CFE’s respective priorities, in December 2025, we agreed to terminate the existing development agreement.’ Image: Shutterstock]]></description>
