		<item>
		<title>Wah Kwong, CIMC and CMES in Hong Kong’s green methanol bunkering first</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/energy/methanol/hong-kong-green-methanol-bunkering-wah-kwong-cmes-cimc/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ariane Morrissey]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 12:37:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Information]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Methanol]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167211</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Hong Kong hosted its first green methanol bunkering operation yesterday (5 March), with Wah Kwong’s bunkering vessel Daqing 268 supplying 500 tonnes of fuel to CM Hong Kong, a dual-fuel Ro-Ro vessel owned by China Merchants Energy Shipping (CMES). The bunkering, which was carried out via a ship-to-ship transfer, ‘confirms Hong Kong’s capability to support green methanol bunkering and marks the city’s entry into a new phase of sustainable marine fuel supply,’ Wah Kwong said in a statement. The green methanol was supplied by CIMC Enric and delivered via Sinopec’s bunkering service network. The fuel has obtained ISCC EU certification, [&#8230;]]]></description>
