		<item>
		<title>US issues temporary waiver on India’s Russian oil purchases</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/information/us-issues-temporary-waiver-on-india-russian-oil-purchases/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Lesley Bankes-Hughes]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 11:54:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Fossil Fuels]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Information]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Regional]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167185</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[The US Department of the Treasury&#8217;s Office of Foreign Assets Control (OFAC) has issued General Licence 133, which will enable India to purchase Russian oil cargoes which are currently on vessels at sea. India currently receives around 40% of its oil requirements from the Middle East but this supply has been interrupted because of hostilities in the region, particularly in the Strait of Hormuz, and so India is urgently looking for crude oil volumes to meet its domestic demand. The temporary waiver began yesterday (5 March) and will cease on 4 April. All deliveries of Russian crude oil or petroleum [&#8230;]]]></description>
