		<item>
		<title>MPA conducts TTX for dual-fuel methanol Disney Adventure</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/energy/mpa-conducts-ttx-for-dual-fuel-methanol-disney-adventure/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rhys Berry]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 11:31:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Methanol]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Ports]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167181</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[The Maritime and Port Authority of Singapore (MPA) recently conducted a multi-agency Table-top Exercise (TTX) ahead of the maiden sailing of the dual-fuel methanol&#160;Disney Adventure&#160;from Singapore. The exercise brought together government agencies and industry partners, including Disney Cruise Line and Marina Bay Cruise Centre Singapore, to review response procedures and strengthen coordination across agencies, MPA said in a social media post today (6 March). ‘Participants worked through a simulated scenario involving a passenger vessel emergency at sea, including an engine-room fire, loss of power, grounding, and listing,’ the MPA said. ‘The discussion focused on key areas such as emergency response, [&#8230;]]]></description>
