		<item>
		<title>Korean Register adds new ammonia-readiness section to its to Technical Rules for low-flashpoint fuels</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/energy/korean-register-adds-new-ammonia-readiness-section-to-its-to-technical-rules-for-low-flashpoint-fuels/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Ian Taylor]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 11:11:35 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Ammonia]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167163</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Korean Register has today (6 March) announced that it has added a new section on ammonia ready vessels to its Technical Rules for the Classification of Ships Using Low-flashpoint Fuels. The newly-established annex on ‘Requirements for Ammonia Fuel Ready’ applies to ‘ships which are prepared for conversion with the design or the partial installation related with ammonia fuel during the new building phase’. It is published as Section 21 of the newly-revised Annex 7 on Requirements for Ships Using Ammonia as Fuel. Click here to download the KR circular with updated Technical Rules. Image: Shutterstock]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="pmpro">
<div class="pmpro_card">
<div class="login-box_wrap container-fluid">
<div class="row">
<div class="col-12 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center my-3">
<h2><strong>Membership Required:</strong> Standard <span class="h2" style>Free</span></h2>
</p></div>
<div class="col-12 mb-3">
<p>You need to be a Standard member to access this content.</p>
