		<item>
		<title>Maersk and Avenir ink bio-LNG supply agreement</title>
		<link>https://ship.energy/energy/maersk-and-avenir-ink-bio-lng-supply-agreement/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rhys Berry]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 10:39:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Biofuel]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Energy]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LNG]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ship.energy/?p=167149</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Avenir LNG subsidiary Avenir Marine Limited has signed a framework bio-LNG supply agreement with A.P. Moller &#8211; Maersk. Under the agreement, which was signed in H2 2025, the companies will begin the supply of bio-LNG in 2027, Avenir LNG said in a social media post today (6 March). ‘The first deliveries will be in alignment with the delivery of the first dual-fuel liquefied gas vessels entering Maersk’s time-chartered fleet,’ Avenir LNG said. As previously reported by ship.energy,&#160;having previously ruled out investing in LNG-powered&#160;vessels, the container shipping giant signed a contract in 2024 for&#160;20 container vessels equipped with LNG dual-fuel engines. [&#8230;]]]></description>
